docs.abstract: Visits to General Motors plants by Mary Barra this year, ahead of contract talks, did not engender as much harmony as the company might have hoped.
docs.snippet: Visits to General Motors plants by Mary Barra this year, ahead of contract talks, did not engender as much harmony as the company might have hoped.
docs.lead_paragraph: Mary T. Barra has often referred to her years of experience on the General Motors factory floor. So it was familiar terrain when the chief executive embarked this year on a tour of plants across the Midwest and South, a mission to create good will among unionized workers ahead of contract talks.

headline.main: G.M. Chief’s Test: Satisfy Striking Workers and Sustain Bottom Line
headline.print_headline: Job Facing G.M. Chief Only Gets Tougher
